","value":"PQC Migration for Derived PIV Credentials","position":{"start":{"line":104,"column":1},"end":{"line":104,"column":1}},"key":"OmaBIjbKK1"}],"identifier":"pqc-migration-for-derived-piv-credentials","label":"PQC Migration for Derived PIV Credentials","html_id":"pqc-migration-for-derived-piv-credentials","implicit":true,"key":"Bf1hOUjRpk"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":106,"column":1},"end":{"line":106,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"cite","url":"https://doi.org/10.6028/NIST.SP.800-157r1.fpd","position":{"start":{"line":106,"column":1},"end":{"line":106,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"SP 800-157r1","position":{"start":{"line":106,"column":1},"end":{"line":106,"column":1}},"key":"kAj50cstZQ"}],"kind":"narrative","label":"Ferraiolo_2024","identifier":"https://doi.org/10.6028/NIST.SP.800-157r1.fpd","enumerator":"1","key":"l0AffZjw2k"},{"type":"text","value":" specifies derived PIV credentials — additional cryptographic authenticators that are issued to a PIV cardholder and bound to their PIV identity account. Derived PIV credentials extend PIV authentication beyond the PIV Card, accommodating both PKI-based credentials and non-PKI phishing-resistant authenticators such as those supporting WebAuthn and FIDO standards. Derived PIV credentials are issued based on the same identity proofing process as the PIV Card and are managed centrally alongside the cardholder’s other PIV credentials.","position":{"start":{"line":106,"column":1},"end":{"line":106,"column":1}},"key":"Q51NnZkyoP"}],"key":"CHBc1jRxfw"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":108,"column":1},"end":{"line":108,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"SP 800-157r1 will need to be updated to permit and reference PQC-capable authenticators and certificates. However, the integration of PQC into the cryptographic authenticators, authentication protocols, certificate profiles, and network security protocols used by derived PIV credentials will primarily be addressed in the base standards and profiles for those mechanisms. For PKI-based derived PIV credentials, the cryptographic updates will follow from changes to SP 800-78 and the Federal PKI Common Policy Framework. For non-PKI-based derived PIV credentials, PQC support will depend on the adoption of PQC algorithms in the underlying authenticator and protocol standards (e.g., WebAuthn, FIDO, TLS).","position":{"start":{"line":108,"column":1},"end":{"line":108,"column":1}},"key":"PaPxztq1cO"}],"key":"JaMfSpeBLD"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"enumerated":false,"position":{"start":{"line":110,"column":1},"end":{"line":110,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"PQC Migration for Federation","position":{"start":{"line":110,"column":1},"end":{"line":110,"column":1}},"key":"qJWddjgmn1"}],"identifier":"pqc-migration-for-federation","label":"PQC Migration for Federation","html_id":"pqc-migration-for-federation","implicit":true,"key":"MWQ3V3I4xf"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":112,"column":1},"end":{"line":112,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"cite","url":"https://doi.org/10.6028/NIST.SP.800-217.fpd","position":{"start":{"line":112,"column":1},"end":{"line":112,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"SP 800-217","position":{"start":{"line":112,"column":1},"end":{"line":112,"column":1}},"key":"xU4LmV3B5Q"}],"kind":"narrative","label":"Ferraiolo_2024","identifier":"https://doi.org/10.6028/NIST.SP.800-217.fpd","enumerator":"1","key":"yMUTe4Hc7p"},{"type":"text","value":" provides guidelines for PIV federation — the use of federation protocols to communicate identity attributes and authentication information across organizational boundaries, enabling PIV cardholders to authenticate to relying parties through identity providers that verify PIV credentials and issue federated assertions.","position":{"start":{"line":112,"column":1},"end":{"line":112,"column":1}},"key":"sBZZn0g5oN"}],"key":"aoNJf7yw0O"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":114,"column":1},"end":{"line":114,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"SP 800-217 will need to be updated to accommodate PQC algorithms in its requirements for assertion signing, assertion encryption, bound authenticators, and supporting network security. However, the integration of PQC into federation will primarily be addressed in the base standards and profiles for the federation protocols (e.g., OpenID Connect, SAML), the cryptographic libraries and key management practices used by identity providers and relying parties, and the network security protocols (e.g., TLS) that protect federation transactions.","position":{"start":{"line":114,"column":1},"end":{"line":114,"column":1}},"key":"NtoQkNjUTW"}],"key":"X3lwKPw3eU"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"enumerated":false,"position":{"start":{"line":116,"column":1},"end":{"line":116,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Summary","position":{"start":{"line":116,"column":1},"end":{"line":116,"column":1}},"key":"EBavOyEfME"}],"identifier":"summary","label":"Summary","html_id":"summary","implicit":true,"key":"hJalNEmFbb"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":118,"column":1},"end":{"line":118,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Support for PQC in PIV is expected to require coordinated updates across the PIV algorithm profile, command interface, data model, derived credential guidelines, and federation guidelines. Interoperability will require the coexistence of classical and PQC mechanisms during the migration period, and the specification updates are expected to preserve existing classical structures while adding support for PQC keys and associated data objects.","position":{"start":{"line":118,"column":1},"end":{"line":118,"column":1}},"key":"kmZpzzzX3O"}],"key":"uoz0PbyMO6"}],"key":"GVyacAJwkn"}],"key":"RBKq971xND"},"references":{"cite":{"order":["Ferraiolo_2024"],"data":{"Ferraiolo_2024":{"label":"Ferraiolo_2024","enumerator":"1","doi":"10.6028/nist.sp.800-217.fpd","html":"Ferraiolo, H., Regenscheid, A., & Richer, J. (2024). <i>Guidelines for Personal Identity Verification (PIV) Federation</i>. National Institute of Standards. <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\" href=\"https://doi.org/10.6028/nist.sp.800-217.fpd\">10.6028/nist.sp.800-217.fpd</a>","url":"https://doi.org/10.6028/nist.sp.800-217.fpd"}}}},"footer":{"navigation":{"prev":{"title":"PIV Standards and Guidelines","short_title":"PIV Standards and Guidelines","url":"/","group":"PIV Standards and Guidelines"},"next":{"title":"Interfaces for Personal Identity Verification (Working Draft)","short_title":"800-73pt1– PIV Card Application Namespace, Data Model, and Representation","url":"/sp800-73pt1","group":"PIV Standards and Guidelines"}}},"domain":"http://localhost:3000"}